cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of improving network availability in ultra-reliable and low-latency communications, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a framework to maximize available range, which involves system optimization and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper considers the impact of correlated shadowing and processing delay, which are related to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and multimedia (cs.MM), respectively.
